Hi, I have developed a Jmeter script to monitor jira performance in our production instance. The script consists of just one thread which logs into the application (once at the beginning of the script) and opens an issue (always the same issue, an easy one with no subtasks, no links, ...) every 30 seconds

Until today I was using my own jira user to run the test. My jira user is not admin but is in a lot of roles, groups, etc. But today I had to send the script to a colleague  at another city and created an internal user with the minimal permissions needed to log in and browse the issue

The surprise is that the performance difference is amazing from using one user to the other. ¿Is this the expected behavior?

