There is an annoying BUG regarding (Release) date processing. If one edits a version to set a Release date, it displays that date as MMM/dd/yyyy (at least for us Americans). But if one later selects the gear to the right and requests to mark the version as Released, the date is still supplied as MMM/dd/yyyy, which is considered to be an incorrect format. Nevertheless, the system fully understands the meaning of that date. If one clicks on the calendar icon, it knows what date is meant. If one then clicks on that date in the calendar, it is rewritten in the expected acceptable format. So the code understands the date, but it still makes the human go through extra steps to get it into a format that it prefers over the original format that it supplied itself. The inconsistency is in the code and unnecessary. (Optional side observation: Why don't you consider storing/processing dates using the clear international standard of yyyy/mm/dd, which is unambiguous and sorts correctly even as text?)

