The JIRA installer should offer the user the option to NOT restart JIRA if customizations have been made.

When running JIRA installer & choosing "upgrade", the process provides a complete listing of all the customizations that will be impacted by the upgrade... stuff that will have manually migrated.  The installer then does exactly what the documentation says...

{quote}
i.   Back up your existing JIRA installation.
ii    Delete the contents of the existing JIRA installation directory.
iii.  Install the new version of JIRA to the existing JIRA installation directory.
iv.  Starts your new (upgraded) JIRA installation.
{quote}

The automatic start-up can cause nothing but problems for a customized installation.  At the very least, it adds several minutes to the upgrade process as you have to shut down JIRA in order to perform the manual migrations.

If the wizard did not automatically restart JIRA then maybe JRA-30340 would be addressed.

